@startuml sie-description-query-uc-v1

' ============================================================
' VISUAL THEME
' ============================================================

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam ArrowColor #57606A
skinparam DefaultFontName "SansSerif"
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam actorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam actorBorderColor #57606A

skinparam usecaseBackgroundColor #F6F8FA
skinparam usecaseBorderColor #57606A

skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #57606A

skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8C5
skinparam noteBorderColor #57606A

' ============================================================

title UC - SIE Description Query + View Contracts - v1

note as FeasibilityNote
  **SAFe mapping:** Enabler Epic EN-1 Evidence, Trace, Provenance runway
  Capability: Description Query + View Contracts
  Feature: Description selectors + snapshot contracts

  **Plane ownership:** Description plane (sensor + comparator substrate).
  Definition plane and Governance mechanisms consume description snapshots
  to ground decisions and produce replayable deliverables.

  **Interface grounding:** observation -> governance `getDescription(selector)`
  (wrapped as `DescriptionQueryEvent` + snapshot response).

  **Requires capabilities:** Evidence+State substrate, Security+Access,
  Versioning+Provenance, Instrumentation+Trace.

  **Feasibility tier:** NOW
end note

' ============================================================
' ACTORS
' ============================================================

actor "Policy Author" as PolicyAuthor
actor "Governance Officer" as GovOfficer
actor "Operator" as Operator
actor "Auditor" as Auditor

actor "Description Store" as DescStore <<system>>
actor "Snapshot Builder" as SnapshotBuilder <<system>>
actor "Access Control (View Contract)" as AccessControl <<system>>
actor "Provenance Store" as ProvStore <<system>>

' ============================================================
' USE CASES
' ============================================================

rectangle "Description Query + View Contracts" {

  package "Description Snapshot" {
    usecase "Request Description\nSnapshot" as UC_RequestSnapshot
    usecase "Apply Selector\n(scope + time)" as UC_ApplySelector
    usecase "Enforce View Contract\n(redaction + shaping)" as UC_ViewContract
    usecase "Attach Provenance\n(lineage + versions)" as UC_AttachProv
    usecase "Support Replayable\nDescription Queries" as UC_Replayable
  }
}

' ============================================================
' RELATIONSHIPS - Actors to Use Cases
' ============================================================

PolicyAuthor --> UC_RequestSnapshot
PolicyAuthor --> UC_Replayable

GovOfficer --> UC_RequestSnapshot
GovOfficer --> UC_AttachProv

Operator --> UC_RequestSnapshot
Operator --> UC_ViewContract

Auditor --> UC_Replayable
Auditor --> UC_AttachProv

' ============================================================
' RELATIONSHIPS - System Actors
' ============================================================

UC_RequestSnapshot --> DescStore
UC_RequestSnapshot --> SnapshotBuilder
UC_ApplySelector --> SnapshotBuilder
UC_ViewContract --> AccessControl
UC_AttachProv --> ProvStore
UC_Replayable --> DescStore

' ============================================================
' RELATIONSHIPS - Include/Extend
' ============================================================

UC_RequestSnapshot ..> UC_ApplySelector : <<include>>
UC_RequestSnapshot ..> UC_ViewContract : <<include>>
UC_RequestSnapshot ..> UC_AttachProv : <<include>>
UC_Replayable ..> UC_RequestSnapshot : <<include>>

' ============================================================
' NOTES
' ============================================================

note right of UC_ApplySelector
  **Selector dimensions (example)**

  - scope: {services, risks, constraints}
  - time: {now | asOf(timestamp) | range}
  - granularity: {raw | derived | summary}
  - bounds: {maxRows, maxDepth}
end note

note right of UC_ViewContract
  **View contract examples**

  - role-based field redaction
  - tenant isolation
  - purpose limitation (audit vs ops)
  - derived-only summaries when raw is restricted
end note

@enduml
